# Choosing compute — the cheat sheet

The exam hands you a workload and asks which compute fits. Match the *shape* of the work:

- **Interactive dev / ad-hoc notebooks** → **all-purpose cluster** — stays up, shared, rerun as you iterate
- **Scheduled production ETL** → **job cluster** — spins up per run, isolated, cheaper job rate
- **BI dashboards & ad-hoc SQL** → **SQL warehouse** (prefer **serverless** for the fastest start)
- **Bursty or hands-off work** → **serverless compute** — seconds to start, no idle cost
- **ML training** → **all-purpose or job cluster on the ML runtime** (ML libraries, GPUs)

The throughline: interactive & shared → all-purpose · scheduled & isolated → job · SQL & BI → warehouse · spiky & hands-off → serverless.
